The paper deals with the analysis of algorithms for solving the shortest vector problem in lattices, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and cryptography. This makes it likely to belong to the categories of cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). However, since the paper focuses on the analysis of algorithms and their complexity, cs.DS and cs.CC are the most likely categories. The paper also discusses the practical cost of solving SVP, which could make it relevant to cs.CR and cs.LG as well.
